Hi everyone - I hope this is the right channel for this. With the V2 version of the forms you could edit a few things including the callback. With the new form editor with multi-step and conditional redirects, it appears that option has been removed from the embed code.

```&lt;script src="<https://js-eu1.hsforms.net/forms/embed/145315646.js>" defer&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;div class="hs-form-frame" data-region="eu1" data-form-id="87ea34eb-5caa-4c3e-b1fc-012143abaa98" data-portal-id="145315646"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;```
vs the old

```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
    hbspt.forms.create( {
        portalId: '145315646',
        formId: '87ea34eb-5caa-4c3e-b1fc-012143abaa98',
        region: 'eu1',
        onFormReady: function($form) { }
    });
&lt;/script&gt;```
Will there be a way to modify the callback or onFormReady or the new forms editor?
